OL,3,C'Social media ruined my life' says
OL,4,Cteen amid calls for online child safety
OL,6,FCurrently, social media regulations in
OL,7,Fthe UK restrict children under the age
OL,8,Fof 13 from having social media.
OL,9,FCompanies like Snapchat, Instagram,
OL,10,FFacebook, and TikTok say they have
OL,11,Fmeasures in place to verify the age of
OL,12,Fchildren, as well as ways to restrict
OL,13,Ftheir access to harmful content.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/10
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1772457071
OL,3,C'Social media ruined my life' says
OL,4,Cteen amid calls for online child safety
OL,6,FBut according to Ofcom, it is
OL,7,Festimated that 2.5 million children
OL,8,Funder 13 years of age use social media
OL,9,Fin the UK. In December, Australia
OL,10,Fintroduced a blanket ban on all social
OL,11,Fmedia platforms for children under 16.
OL,12,FNow, there is mounting cross-party
OL,13,Fpressure on the UK Government to do
OL,14,Fthe same.
OL,16,FThe Government has since launched a
OL,17,Fthree-month consultation, with a
OL,18,Fdecision on its outcome expected by
OL,19,Fthe end of the year. The Children's
OL,20,FCommissioner for Wales feels the
OL,21,Fconsultation is necessary.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/10
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1772457071
OL,3,C'Social media ruined my life' says
OL,4,Cteen amid calls for online child safety
OL,6,F"At the moment, it's too early to make
OL,7,Fa decision, but we definitely welcome
OL,8,Fa consultation so everyone can give
OL,9,Ftheir opinion on the matter," says
OL,10,FMabon Huws from the Commissioner's
OL,11,FOffice.
OL,13,FHe explains: "We need more information
OL,14,Ffrom the UK Government; we need to
OL,15,Fknow what the ban means first. The
OL,16,Fissue is that a blanket ban may
OL,17,Fexclude some children from important
OL,18,Fservices and there is a risk that some
OL,19,Fchildren may be directed to the dark
OL,20,Fcorners of the web."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/10
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1772457071
OL,3,C'Social media ruined my life' says
OL,4,Cteen amid calls for online child safety
OL,6,FThe Commissioner's Office also says
OL,7,Fthat the Government should implement
OL,8,Fits existing policies more
OL,9,Feffectively. Mabon says, "We need
OL,10,Fgreater adherence to the Online Safety
OL,11,FBill; we need to enforce it better and
OL,12,Fput more responsibility on the social
OL,13,Fmedia companies to take action."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/10
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
